--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Mathematical methods are reimplemented from their source papers as factual
content (mathematical formulas are not copyrightable), with citations:

  - Bailey, D. H. & Lopez de Prado, M. (2014). "The Deflated Sharpe Ratio:
    Correcting for Selection Bias, Backtest Overfitting and Non-Normality."
  - Bailey, Borwein, Lopez de Prado, Zhu (2017). "The Probability of Backtest
    Overfitting." Journal of Computational Finance.

The single-asset quant factors in `bitarena/perception/factors.py` are
reimplemented in NumPy from the published formulas (factual content) of:
  - Kakushadze, Z. (2015). "101 Formulaic Alphas" (arXiv:1601.00991).
  - Guotai Junan Securities (2014). "191 Short-period Trading Alpha Factors."
  - Microsoft Qlib "Alpha158" feature set (Apache-2.0).
Only formulas are reproduced; no prose, tables, or upstream code.

